        "description": "Not sure this is desirable, since {{util/logging.h}} was taken from glog, but the various debug checks current {{std::exit(1)}} on failure. This is a clean exit (though with an error code) and therefore doesn't trigger the usual debugging tools such as gdb or Python's faulthandler. By replacing it with something like {{std::abort()}} the exit would be recognized as a process crash.\r\n\r\n\u00a0\r\n\r\nThoughts?",
